The paper focuses on measuring and analyzing network coverage of mobile operators in Afghanistan, which falls under the category of network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the relationship between network coverage and end user satisfaction, which could be related to cybersecurity (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the proposed solutions for expanding network coverage and enhancing network performance could be related to systems and control (cs.SI) and cryptography (cs.CY).
